The paper discusses acoustic modeling for automatic speech recognition (ASR) using multi-channel audio input and compression techniques. This falls under the sub-category of Speech and Signal Processing (cs.SD) and Computational Linguistics (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper discusses the optimization of bitrate allocation for different channels, which could fall under the sub-categories of Systems and Control (cs.SY) and Signal Processing (cs.SP). Finally, the paper also discusses the training of the acoustic model on mixed bitrate input, which could fall under the sub-category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI).
